column3: A –a- / –ar- / –aa- / +a- / +aar- to V repeatedly The first three forms (–a-, –ar-, –a-) of this postbase are non-productive, and the occurrences listed here for these three forms are relatively complete for our data. The fourth form (+a-) is used on verb bases not taking one of the first three forms and not ending in te, and the fifth form (+aar-) is used on verb bases ending in te. Form –a- (note that this form does not occur with bases ending in ar- or ag-): qalrir-
